Description: End of Term social at a local Pub. A joint event with Act Sci.

name: Intro to Hadoop
Description: Hadoop is a distributed computing system designed to process information beyond the processing limitations to SQL databases: Tetrabyes, Petrabytes, etc. Hadoop and related tools are the data analysis platform used for "big data". Such companies that use Hadoop include: Facebook, Amazon, ebay, Google, LinkedIn, Twitter.

name: Intro to SQL
Description:
SQL is a relational database language and along with R and Python is among the most popular data analysis tools and one of the most in-demand skills for 2014.

The talk will touch on the theory behind relational databases and various ways of querying a SQL database with short quizzes in between. Food will be available to Stats Club Members ($2).

name: Prof Talk: Machine Learning
Description: Machine Learning and Data Mining: How We can Change the World
